    <p> Friendship bracelets have a rich history dating back centuries, originating from various cultures around the world. However, they gained significant popularity in the 1970s as a symbol of friendship and unity. Traditionally crafted from colorful threads or yarn, these bracelets were handmade and exchanged between friends as tokens of love and camaraderie. The intricate patterns and weaving techniques varied widely depending on cultural influences, with each bracelet holding unique significance. Over time, friendship bracelet making evolved into a cherished craft enjoyed by people of all ages, fostering connections and memories that last a lifetime.</p>
